I just wanna thank you for the motivation, Lily. I'm having some doubts about my future as a scholar. I'm not sure whether I have it to make it, because there seems to be so many people who are much better and much more passionate about it than me. I just can't seem to be passionate even in the one thing I can picture myself loving. And my society is not very friendly to women in the workplace so basically I have to be noticeably better than my male peers to succeed and reach the top. I know that when speaking about social problems you shouldn't put it on the individuals to break through, but your video made me realize that when it's about yourself, you should face the problems upfront and not make excuses about it. Sorry if my words were not coherent, but I just wanted to get it out there and make a New Year's resolution.
